en_106757_0	The Court of Appeal today issued an interim order suspending the Gazette notification on banning the use of full-face helmets, until April 28th.
en_106757_1	The ban on wearing full-face helmets, was to be implemented from today initially as a ‘warning opportunity’.
en_106757_2	However, when a petition filed by two individuals challenging the ban was taken up for hearing today, a bench of appeal court judges issued the interim order.
